The paper deals with optimization of automatic gain control and linear receive filter for large-scale multi-user MIMO systems with coarsely quantized signals in cloud radio access networks. This involves signal processing, communication theory, and network infrastructure, which are all relevant to the sub-categories of Information Theory (cs.IT), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), and Systems and Control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of successive interference cancellation receivers, which falls under the sub-category of Multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper deals with cloud radio access networks, which is a topic related to Computer Communications (cs.COM).
